The paper discusses the vulnerability of a specific blockchain protocol to Sybil attacks, which is a well-known security issue in computer networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the scalability issues of blockchain protocols, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves numerical simulations, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
